  "instructions": [
    "Cut the eggplant into 1-inch cubes and set aside.",
    "Heat the olive oil in a large skillet over medium heat.",
    "Add the onion and cook until softened, about 5 minutes.",
    "Add the garlic, cumin, smoked paprika, salt, and black pepper, and cook for 1 minute.",
    "Add the eggplant and cook, stirring occasionally, until tender, about 10 minutes.",
    "Add the split peas, 2 cups of water, and bring to a boil.",
    "Reduce heat to low, cover, and simmer for 20 minutes or until the peas are tender.",
    "Serve the pea-eggplant mixture in a stone bowl, garnished with chopped parsley and topped with grated cheese if desired."
